Which Class acts as a root for all JAVA Exceptions?
Answer: Throwable Class

There are two Child Classes of Throwable:

    1. Exception
    2. Error



Exception vs Error:

Exception:
Most of the Time Exceptions are cause by our Program. Exceptions are recovorable and can be handled

Error:
Most of the times errors are not caused by program. Errors are due to lack of system Resources. Example Stack OVerflowError. It Can't be handled


Exception Child Class:
1. Runtime Exception
    a. Arethemic Exception
    b. Null Pointer Exception
    c. ClassNotFoundException
    d. IndexOutOfBound Exception
        - ArrayIndexOutOfBoundException
        - StringIndexOutOfBoundException
    e. IllegalArgumentException

2. IOException
    a. EOFException
    b. FileNotFoundException
    c. InterruptedIOExcetpion
3. Servlet Exception
4. Remote Exception
5. Interrupted Exception



Error:
    a. VM Error
        - StackOverflowError
        - OutOfMemoryError
    b. AssertionError
    c. ExceptionInInititalizerError
